cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptive person re-identification, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for learning a re-ID model, which involves memory-based techniques and enforcing invariance constraints. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves techniques for generalizing the re-ID model with respect to different types of invariance, which may fall under categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
